SIMPLE: overboard
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overboard
<hw>O"ver*board`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Over the side
of a ship; hence, from on board of a ship, into the water; <as>as, to
fall <ex>overboard</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To throw overboard</b></col>, <cd>to discard; to abandon,
as a dependent or friend.</cd> -- <col><b>To go overboard</b></col>,
<cd>to go to an extreme; to overdo; <as>as, he <ex>went overboard</ex>
at the buffet and got an upset stomach</as>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overboil</ent>⟦br⟧
